frameDefinitions: An Agent succeeds or fails to interact perceptually or physically with the Target or Target_location.
One linguistic unit, Sign_1, has a relation to another linguistic unit, Sign_2.

The answer to one open question, the Outcome, is dictated (partially or completely) by the answer to another open question, the Determinant, i.e. if the answer to the Determinant is known, the answer to the Outcome can be predicted.
A Political_region, often a nation,  has an economic system, theEconomy, defined by the level of production and consumption of goods and services.
This frame contains items which, when manipulated, alter the function of some device, internal or external.
A concept, Concept_1, is related causally or collocationally to another concept, Concept_2 by means of some evidence.
frameExamples: At first he shot very <t>wide</t> of his target .
Economic policy is partially a <t>function</t> of cultural values.
The Canadian <t><fex name='Economy'>economy</fex></t> will continue to expand in 2005.
This <t>button</t> makes the radio turn on.
listRoleDefinitions: The individual who tries to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
The <fen>Target</fen> is the entity located in an indirectly accessible location relative to the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The object manipulated by the <fen>Agent</fen> in order to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
The location that the <fen>Agent</fen> is attempting to access using the <fen>Instrument</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when something hits or misses.
The place where the <fen>Agent</fen> manages or fails to interact with the <fen>Target</fen>.
FN: a linguistic unit that carries semantic, phonological or syntactic information.
An open question that is (to some degree) predictable from the Determinant.
An open question that determines the <fen>Outcome</fen>.
The <fen>Political_region</fen> is the nation, state, or other political body within which an economic system exists.
The <fen>Economy</fen> is the state of the <fen>Political_region</fen> as defined by the production, consumption, etc. of goods and services.
This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>. This is often an incorporated FE.
The concept which is linked to <fen>Concept_2</fen>.  Generally expressed as the external argument.
The concept which is tied to <fen>Concept_1</fen>.  Generally expressed as a PP complement.
listRoleExamples: In one sense, <fex>dog</fex> is a hyponym of itself.
In one sense, dog is a hyponym of <fex>itself</fex>.
Price, in such a case, depends <fex>only on the whim of the supplier</fex>.
